Answer: $5$ dm
Explanation: >
  Volume setengah = $60$ liter ($dm^3$). Volume total = $60 \times 2 = 120$ $dm^3$.
  Volume = $p \times l \times t \Rightarrow 120 = 6 \times 4 \times t \Rightarrow 120 = 24 \times t \Rightarrow t = 5$ dm.
